\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Parameter Estimation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are various ways to estimate parameters of Markov regime swiching
 model.
 E-M algorithm, segmental K-mean 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "juang1990segmental"

\end_inset

, Gibbs sampling 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "kim1999state"

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
In this study, E-M algorithm will be focused on estimating 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
Filtered and smoothing probability
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
The Expectation-Maximization algorithm
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
the set of parameter is estimated by iterative two-step procedure.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
start with an arbitrary initial parameters
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
repeat these two steps until the maximum value of the likelihood function
 is obtained
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
E-step
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
filtering and smoothing
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
calculate the expectation of 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{t}$
\end_inset

 under the current estimation of the parameters
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
M-step
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
obtain new estimates parameters by estimating linear model for each state
 conditioning on the values for 
\begin_inset Formula $S_{t}$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citep
key "janczura2012efficient"

\end_inset


\end_layout

